CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1961, pg. A6 reads: "Gift For Grand Master - District Deputy Grand Masters make a presentation to Most Worshipful Grand Master A. William Hill Jr., PHA, during the banquet, recently, at the Hotel Penn-Sheraton, in Pittsburgh. Left to right: Hassel A. Walton, 11th District; Howard Lewis, Fifth District; James H. King, Seventh District; Jesse L. Cunningham, Fourth District; Grand Master Hill; Albert Letson, First District; Major A. Greene, Seventh District, making the presentation; John Taylor, Eighth District; the Rev. Thomas Logan, First District; William A. Harris,  First District; John Julett, First District, and Edgar C. Patience, Ninth District."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of twelve Masons, from left: Hassel A. Walton, Howard Lewis, James H. King, Jesse L. Cunningham, Albert Letson, Major A. Greene, making presentation to A. William Hill; John Taylor, Rev. Thomas Logan, William A. Harris, John Julett, and Edgar C. Patience, standing behind large banquet table, including two men wearing light colored dinner jackets, standing at podium during th Prince Hall Grand Lodge banquet in the Penn Sheraton hotel
